Power Supply:

* USB, provided by host PC  
* External Source  
  * Vin: 7-12V  
  * E5V: 5V  
  * C6 or C7: 3.3V  
* Max current is configured through jumpers 

LEDs:

* LD1 \- tricolor (green, orange, red) \- ST-LINK comm status   
* LD2 \- green user pin  
  * PA5 (pin 21\)   
* LD3 \- PWR. Red LED indicating STM32 is powered and 5V is available 

Push Buttons:

* B1 \- User, connected to PC13 (pin2)  
* B2 \- Reset. Connected to NRST

OSC Clock:

* OSC Clock Supply  
  * Four ways to configure pins corresponding to external high speed clock (HSE): MCO from ST-LINK, HSE oscillator from on-board X3 crystal, oscillator from external PF0/PD0/PH0, or HSE not used   
  * Board version MB1136-F446RE-C04, so default configuration is to use ST-LINK MCO as clock input   
* OSC 32KHz Clock Supply  
  * Three possible configurations for low speed clock (LSE): on-board oscillator X2 crystal, oscillator from external PC14, or LSE not used  
  * Board version MB1136-F446RE-C04, so default configuration is to use on-board 32KHz oscillator
